hopobject.body: I'm at Liverpool University little griddle nanuet menu It isn’t the markets it is the hyperbole and spin from all the talking heads. When grocery stores close and two of the worlds largest retailers (JCP & Macys) have bad times then you are observing the real feelings of consumers around spendable income. Cars are selling because leases and deals have never been better and they need to just “move units” off their lots. The improving economy is only a mirage when 7.6 million Americans have quit and been removed from the unemployment figures because of it.
